properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 17 at 2:49PM CST until January 19 at 12:00AM CST by NWS Duluth MN
properties.description:
...HEAVY SNOW TO RAMP UP THIS AFTERNOON INTO SATURDAY...

.Moderate to heavy snow will increase through the rest of the
afternoon and evening, spreading north and east. This snow will
become widespread tonight, and last into Saturday morning. The
heavy snow will gradually decrease from southwest to northeast
through the day Saturday. Total snowfall for most locations will
range between 5 to 10 inches, with higher amounts expected along
the higher terrain of the North Shore, where over 12"+ of snow
will be possible. In addition to the snow, gusty southeasterly
winds will occur today into this evening, then strong northwest
winds will occur Saturday. The wind will cause blowing and
drifting snow, especially on Saturday. Hazardous travel conditions
are expected.

* WHAT...Heavy snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 6 to 9
inches, with heavier amounts possible along the higher
elevations of northern Iron county. Winds gusting as high as 25
to 35 mph this evening and especially on Saturday.

* WHERE...Iron county in northwest Wisconsin.

* WHEN...Until midnight CST Saturday night.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult at times. The
hazardous conditions could impact the Friday evening commute.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

The latest road conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1. Road
conditions can also be found at 511mn.org for Minnesota or
511wi.gov for Wisconsin.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL MIDNIGHT CST SATURDAY NIGHT
